A resource is a single infrastructure object managed by Terraform: an S3 bucket, an RDS instance, a VPC, an IAM role, etc.

Syntax:
```hcl
resource "<PROVIDER>_<TYPE>" "<LOCAL_NAME>" {
  argument1 = value1
  argument2 = value2
}
```

Example: S3 bucket for a data lake:
```hcl
resource "aws_s3_bucket" "data_lake" {
  bucket = "my-company-data-lake"

  tags = {
    Environment = "production"
    Team        = "data-engineering"
  }
}

resource "aws_s3_bucket_versioning" "data_lake" {
  bucket = aws_s3_bucket.data_lake.id
  versioning_configuration {
    status = "Enabled"
  }
}
```

Reference pattern: aws_s3_bucket.data_lake.id
- First part: resource type (aws_s3_bucket)
- Second part: local name (data_lake)
- Third part: exported attribute (id, arn, bucket, etc.)

Terraform tracks every resource in state so it can detect changes on next plan.
